00:51:22,700 --> 00:51:25,134
They overcook and ruin the lamb.

540
00:51:25,620 --> 00:51:27,929
Am I doing this right?

541
00:51:29,860 --> 00:51:31,134
Yes.

542
00:51:31,660 --> 00:51:32,809
Girls.

543
00:51:34,140 --> 00:51:35,129
Try that. No?

544
00:51:35,220 --> 00:51:36,255
No, we don't eat that, but thanks.

545
00:51:36,500 --> 00:51:37,979
No? All right.

546
00:51:39,140 --> 00:51:40,812
That stuff stinks.

547
00:51:41,980 --> 00:51:44,289
We've been using the wrong bait.

548
00:51:44,860 --> 00:51:46,737
- Try this here.
- Oh, yeah.

549
00:51:46,820 --> 00:51:48,776
- You know what, give me one.
- Here we go.

550
00:51:48,860 --> 00:51:51,090
I got it. Give me that one.

551
00:51:51,180 --> 00:51:53,216
- Give it here.
- Oh, so good.

552
00:51:54,020 --> 00:51:55,931
It's okay. Try that.

553
00:51:56,300 --> 00:51:57,415
Go on.

554
00:51:57,660 --> 00:51:58,649
Yeah.

555
00:51:58,740 --> 00:52:00,890
First peanuts, and now this.

556
00:52:01,540 --> 00:52:05,010
- Here you go, ladies.
- Try some of Mr Ritter's biscuits.

557
00:52:05,220 --> 00:52:07,529
All right, come on. Thank you.

558
00:52:18,500 --> 00:52:22,049
I tell you, Nephew,
we were fishing with the wrong bait.

559
00:52:22,340 --> 00:52:24,251
Go in there, Hank.
And now, One, Two, Three, Four.

560
00:52:24,340 --> 00:52:25,978
Where's Number Two?

561
00:52:26,060 --> 00:52:29,291
Gilpin, cut one of them biscuits in half,
put some more jam on it for Number Two.

562
00:52:29,380 --> 00:52:31,211
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah.

563
00:52:31,300 --> 00:52:33,734
Where is Number Two? Where's she at?

564
00:52:52,380 --> 00:52:54,098
She don't look good.

565
00:52:55,500 --> 00:52:57,377
Hell, man, she's on fire.

566
00:53:08,420 --> 00:53:09,978
Is she dying?

567
00:53:15,260 --> 00:53:17,376
Hank, what do you make of this?

568
00:53:18,420 --> 00:53:19,773
What's that?

569
00:53:29,260 --> 00:53:30,534
Let's see.

570
00:53:34,820 --> 00:53:36,048
That's a tick.

571
00:53:36,460 --> 00:53:38,178
Probably tick fever.

572
00:53:39,100 --> 00:53:40,419
That ain't good.

573
00:53:40,500 --> 00:53:44,095
No, it's as bad as milk fever is
in young ones.

574
00:53:45,140 --> 00:53:48,530
Let me go get these girls
and we'll check them for ticks, too.

575
00:53:48,620 --> 00:53:51,180
- What else can I do?
- You're doing it.

576
00:53:51,940 --> 00:53:55,933
You got any pull with the Almighty,
you might wanna speak up for her.

577
00:53:56,500 --> 00:54:00,459
We're not properly equipped or suited
to take care of these girls, I tell you.

578
00:55:03,780 --> 00:55:05,338
Let's pay our respects.

579
00:55:08,100 --> 00:55:09,249
Mai Ling.

580
00:55:12,460 --> 00:55:16,339
We wish you a good journey.

581
00:55:19,260 --> 00:55:20,375
Come on.

582
00:55:29,220 --> 00:55:32,417
Goodbye, Mai Ling, little sister.

583
00:55:40,540 --> 00:55:42,815
You have anything you want to say?

584
00:55:46,140 --> 00:55:47,732
Said it last night.

585
00:55:50,020 --> 00:55:51,089
Okay.

586
00:55:58,740 --> 00:56:00,731
The second time I've done this.

587
00:56:00,820 --> 00:56:02,492
It don't get any easier.

588
00:56:04,780 --> 00:56:06,691
We're all travellers in this world.

589
00:56:08,620 --> 00:56:11,054
From the sweet grass to the packing house.

590
00:56:14,980 --> 00:56:16,572
Birth till death.

591
00:56:17,740 --> 00:56:20,413
We travel between the eternities.

592
00:56:56,740 --> 00:56:57,809
Nephew.

593
00:57:28,180 --> 00:57:29,249
Whoa.

594
00:57:30,140 --> 00:57:31,255
Whoa.

595
00:57:34,500 --> 00:57:35,694
Howdy.

596
00:57:36,060 --> 00:57:40,338
Horse took a wrong step in a creek
a ways back and snapped his cannon bone.

597
00:58:15,460 --> 00:58:16,529
Whoa!

598
00:58:20,140 --> 00:58:22,859
Got a cheque here. Think you could cash it?

599
00:58:23,780 --> 00:58:27,568
How long's a man got to stay in prison
to come out with $17.45?

600
00:58:28,180 --> 00:58:29,977
Awful nosy, ain't you?

601
00:58:39,260 --> 00:58:41,091
Hitch that team up, and let's go!

602
00:58:41,180 --> 00:58:42,579
- Hey.
- You heard him.

603
00:58:42,660 --> 00:58:43,854
Hey there.

604
00:59:03,340 --> 00:59:05,649
Come here, darling. Have a seat on my lap.

605
00:59:15,980 --> 00:59:19,416
Glad to see your business has been
good to you since I've been away.

606
00:59:19,500 --> 00:59:21,411
Your timing couldn't be any better.

607
00:59:21,500 --> 00:59:23,013
- Really?
- Really.

608
00:59:24,220 --> 00:59:25,972
Remember Billy Fender?

609
00:59:26,300 --> 00:59:28,018
Captain Billy Fender?

610
00:59:28,380 --> 00:59:29,813
That's the one.

611
00:59:30,780 --> 00:59:33,931
That's the kind of a shit-house rat
you always want to stay upwind of.

612
00:59:34,020 --> 00:59:36,693
I don't pay people for taking baths.

613
00:59:36,780 --> 00:59:39,169
I sent him to pick up and deliver back to me

614
00:59:39,260 --> 00:59:42,775
a load of Chinese girls I bought
from an associate in San Francisco.

615
00:59:43,620 --> 00:59:45,451
Well, he's way overdue.

616
00:59:45,940 --> 00:59:49,296
Knowing him, he's probably
drunk on his ass and hobbling all your girls.

617
00:59:50,140 --> 00:59:52,176
I got a proposition for you.

618
00:59:52,940 --> 00:59:53,929
Yep?

619
00:59:54,500 --> 00:59:57,970
I'll pay you to go find him
and bring those girls back to me.

620
01:00:00,380 --> 01:00:01,415
No.

621
01:00:02,620 --> 01:00:03,735
Maybe later.

622
01:00:04,260 --> 01:00:07,218
Right now all I want is a bottle
and some trim.

623
01:00:10,500 --> 01:00:13,333
I got some new gals
I can turn you loose with.

624
01:00:17,300 --> 01:00:18,813
What about Nola?

625
01:00:23,660 --> 01:00:26,015
Is she still around, Nola?

626
01:00:27,700 --> 01:00:29,930
Why don't you try some of the new talent?

627
01:00:33,660 --> 01:00:36,857
I kind of had my mind set on Nola
for some time now.

628
01:00:58,180 --> 01:00:59,659
Coming through.

629
01:01:06,460 --> 01:01:07,734
Hello, Nola.

630
01:01:08,740 --> 01:01:10,298
It's been a while.

631
01:01:10,780 --> 01:01:12,657
Where have you been, Ed?

632
01:01:14,100 --> 01:01:16,136
Oh, I think you know where I've been.

633
01:01:17,060 --> 01:01:19,733
I figured you must have moved on
to other business.

634
01:01:19,820 --> 01:01:21,048
Yeah, right.

635
01:01:21,500 --> 01:01:23,252
Working for the government.

636
01:01:24,220 --> 01:01:25,653
Three cents a day

637
01:01:25,980 --> 01:01:28,494
making little rocks out of big rocks.

638
01:01:32,340 --> 01:01:34,296
Been thinking a lot about you.

639
01:01:35,140 --> 01:01:36,858
Not much else to do.

640
01:01:38,300 --> 01:01:40,177
Does Kate know you're here?

641
01:01:42,740 --> 01:01:43,968
Oh, yeah.

642
01:01:45,060 --> 01:01:47,415
She sent me up especially for you.

643
01:01:57,100 --> 01:01:59,409
You got orders to wear me out.

644
01:02:09,500 --> 01:02:10,774
Come on, boy.

645
01:02:11,100 --> 01:02:12,215
Come on, boy.

646
01:02:14,220 --> 01:02:15,335
Come on.

647
01:02:16,380 --> 01:02:17,779
Come on, boy.

648
01:02:47,420 --> 01:02:48,614
Problem?

649
01:02:48,860 --> 01:02:50,088
Not sure.

650
01:02:54,300 --> 01:02:55,415
Whoa.

651
01:02:56,540 --> 01:02:58,815
Move off to their right. Keep your distance.

652
01:02:58,900 --> 01:03:00,094
Watch me.

653
01:03:00,540 --> 01:03:02,974
- Hank, let's hold up here.
- Yes, sir.

654
01:03:11,420 --> 01:03:13,012
No, don't do that.

655
01:03:14,020 --> 01:03:15,453
Just watch me.

656
01:03:16,860 --> 01:03:18,134
All right.

657
01:03:31,420 --> 01:03:33,251
Hold up there, mister.

658
01:03:33,420 --> 01:03:34,933
Hold up, mister.

659
01:03:35,980 --> 01:03:37,493
Don't I know you?

660
01:03:37,980 --> 01:03:39,413
What's your name?

661
01:03:39,500 --> 01:03:42,810
My name is my own business.
I suggest you tend to yours.

662
01:03:42,900 --> 01:03:44,777
Will you give me the road, sir?

663
01:03:44,860 --> 01:03:45,975
Hold on!

664
01:03:47,940 --> 01:03:49,658
I know who you are.

665
01:03:49,860 --> 01:03:53,170
I go by several names.
I doubt any of them are your concern.

666
01:03:53,460 --> 01:03:56,338
If you refuse to let me pass,
you'll soon learn a few of them.

667
01:03:56,420 --> 01:03:58,570
Well, would one be Jack Ketch?

668
01:03:59,660 --> 01:04:02,970
If that's who you think I am,
then you know better than to block my path.

669
01:04:03,060 --> 01:04:04,857
Hold on there, mister!

670
01:04:23,580 --> 01:04:25,855
Don't let him get away! Kill him.

671
01:04:25,940 --> 01:04:27,658
And you kill his horse.

672
01:04:42,460 --> 01:04:43,654
Big Bob.

673
01:04:54,300 --> 01:04:56,336
I got him. I got him dead centre.

674
01:04:56,420 --> 01:04:58,172
Right through the heart. I got him.

675
01:04:58,260 --> 01:05:01,138
Stay back, Heck. Don't go there, stay back.
I got him.

676
01:05:01,660 --> 01:05:02,775
Yes, sir.

677
01:05:06,460 --> 01:05:09,338
What the hell was that? We killed two men!

678
01:05:09,420 --> 01:05:13,015
About as close as you'll ever get
to seeing the Grim Reaper.

679
01:05:13,100 --> 01:05:15,614
Bullshit. Make sense to me, Uncle.

680
01:05:15,700 --> 01:05:18,612
- Boys, I'm talking death.
- Horseshit.

681
01:05:18,700 --> 01:05:21,373
We just killed two men
and all their livestock!

682
01:05:22,620 --> 01:05:24,690
I told you to stay back!

683
01:05:26,140 --> 01:05:30,133
That there is most likely
the infamous Smallpox Bob. I'm sure of it.

684
01:05:30,220 --> 01:05:33,337
Probably killed more red men than any
one man in the Northwest.

685
01:05:33,420 --> 01:05:36,218
- Hell, I ain't never heard of him.
- I have.

686
01:05:36,300 --> 01:05:40,816
He trades blankets and hides with the tribes,
mostly infected with smallpox.

687
01:05:40,900 --> 01:05:43,289
Smallpox, typhoid, tuberculosis.

688
01:05:43,380 --> 01:05:46,099
He was death travelling the country,
but no more.

689
01:05:46,180 --> 01:05:49,172
Well, if there was ever an evil bastard
worth killing, I reckon he's the one.

690
01:05:49,260 --> 01:05:51,251
No more evil than the ones that hire him.

691
01:05:51,340 --> 01:05:54,935
Boys, I tell you, we gotta tend to this mess.

692
01:06:25,340 --> 01:06:29,015
That's the second rope I've lost
to some worthless son of a bitch.

693
01:06:29,100 --> 01:06:31,489
I'd say both were for a good cause.

694
01:07:05,540 --> 01:07:08,373
You really think that fellow killed
that many Indians, Mr Ritter?

695
01:07:08,460 --> 01:07:10,769
Of course I do, Hank.
That's why I killed him.

696
01:08:08,300 --> 01:08:11,451
What do you think they will do with us?

697
01:08:11,740 --> 01:08:13,856
It's not just up to our protectors.

698
01:08:14,100 --> 01:08:17,729
If we are to live, we must have courage.

699
01:08:18,980 --> 01:08:21,175
I didn't see you help Ye Fung

700
01:08:22,620 --> 01:08:24,656
when that man attacked her.

701
01:08:40,060 --> 01:08:42,449
Look, she is coming.

702
01:08:45,820 --> 01:08:47,219
There. Right up there.

703
01:08:51,660 --> 01:08:54,458
It's only the moon.

704
01:08:56,180 --> 01:08:57,898
You think she will save us?

705
01:08:58,820 --> 01:09:01,892
Ghee Moon, enough. That's enough.

706
01:09:09,620 --> 01:09:11,850
She comes over the fields of our village.

707
01:09:13,020 --> 01:09:14,612
We must be close to home.

708
01:09:16,660 --> 01:09:17,854
You are right.

709
01:09:21,340 --> 01:09:23,058
She will follow us.

710
01:09:24,940 --> 01:09:26,737
And lead us home.

711
01:09:27,340 --> 01:09:29,012
She is barely visible.

712
01:09:29,820 --> 01:09:32,050
But the moon is like us.

713
01:09:33,740 --> 01:09:35,890
Sometimes she has to hide.

714
01:09:38,340 --> 01:09:39,773
But she stands strong.

715
01:09:42,500 --> 01:09:44,411
So we must be good to one another.

716
01:09:47,060 --> 01:09:48,493
We must be brave.

717
01:10:27,580 --> 01:10:28,695
Gilpin.

718
01:10:33,220 --> 01:10:34,289
Hey.

719
01:10:36,940 --> 01:10:38,851
Wake up, it's your shift.

720
01:10:40,420 --> 01:10:42,729
Oh, Lord, I thought I just dozed off.

721
01:10:42,820 --> 01:10:45,209
Yeah. About four hours ago.

722
01:10:51,820 --> 01:10:54,539
Wouldn't mind getting
a full night's sleep sometime soon.

723
01:10:54,620 --> 01:10:56,656
Well, you can when we get to Cariboo.

724
01:10:56,740 --> 01:10:58,219
Are we really going in there?

725
01:10:58,300 --> 01:11:00,336
Yeah. That's what my uncle said.

726
01:11:01,620 --> 01:11:03,611
- Wake me up in four hours.
- Okay.

727
01:11:10,140 --> 01:11:11,255
Damn it.

728
01:13:03,420 --> 01:13:04,978
Herd is pretty settled.

729
01:13:06,620 --> 01:13:08,895
I'll stay out here and watch things.

730
01:13:11,500 --> 01:13:13,889
I want you to take the girls into this town

731
01:13:14,460 --> 01:13:17,930
and see if you can find some
civil authority to take them.

732
01:13:18,020 --> 01:13:19,612
Take Heck with you.

733
01:13:21,220 --> 01:13:24,053
- I thought you'd be the one to do that.
- Well, you thought wrong.

734
01:13:25,180 --> 01:13:26,693
Well, why here? Why now?

735
01:13:26,780 --> 01:13:28,930
Well, you're the one that's so hot
to get rid of them.

736
01:13:29,420 --> 01:13:31,251
- According to who?
- You.

737
01:13:33,100 --> 01:13:35,011
Now just go and get it done.

738
01:13:43,900 --> 01:13:45,219
Why did they argue?

739
01:13:45,340 --> 01:13:46,773
Wait.

740
01:13:50,140 --> 01:13:53,849
Heck, get everybody in the wagon.
We're going into town.

741
01:13:59,260 --> 01:14:02,775
I got to be honest, Tom. I'm not so sure
about this. I think they might...

742
01:14:02,860 --> 01:14:05,579
Well, you know what? I don't have a vote.
You don't have a vote.

743
01:14:06,180 --> 01:14:07,579
That's becoming evident.

744
01:14:08,340 --> 01:14:10,058
Just get them in the wagon.

745
01:14:12,380 --> 01:14:14,735
- All right, ladies. Let's go.
- Tom.

746
01:14:15,860 --> 01:14:17,293
We're going into town.

747
01:14:19,340 --> 01:14:21,217
Let's go, girls, come on.

748
01:15:16,380 --> 01:15:20,658
I still ain't seen Billy Fender
and that load of Chinese girls I bought.

749
01:15:22,580 --> 01:15:25,617
- I'm still offering to pay you to find them.
- No.

750
01:15:26,300 --> 01:15:28,211
I got business of my own in mind.

751
01:15:31,860 --> 01:15:34,420
All you know how to do
is what got you sent up for.

752
01:15:34,500 --> 01:15:36,536
It's small fry that gets sent up.

753
01:15:37,500 --> 01:15:39,297
I'm looking to get big.

754
01:15:40,740 --> 01:15:44,176
- You could be my banker.
- Lf I'm your bank, you're working for me.

755
01:15:47,100 --> 01:15:48,852
You're a good businesswoman.

756
01:15:49,940 --> 01:15:52,056
You know how to get a return
on your investment.

757
01:15:52,940 --> 01:15:55,534
$500 will get me started just fine.

758
01:16:46,620 --> 01:16:47,735
Howdy.

759
01:16:47,820 --> 01:16:49,856
- Whoa.
- Good day to you, sir.

760
01:16:52,660 --> 01:16:54,969
- You be needing a room?
- Yes, sir.

761
01:16:55,420 --> 01:16:57,092
Two rooms for one night.

762
01:16:57,180 --> 01:16:59,136
It's $4, up front.

763
01:16:59,220 --> 01:17:01,051
Is there a mayor in this town?

764
01:17:01,740 --> 01:17:03,093
Not hardly.

765
01:17:03,180 --> 01:17:05,410
- What about a town council?
- Nope.

766
01:17:08,380 --> 01:17:11,577
- Do you have a sheriff?
- No, sir, not anymore.

767
01:17:12,780 --> 01:17:13,929
Mister,

768
01:17:14,780 --> 01:17:17,340
this town is as rough as cob.

769
01:17:17,780 --> 01:17:18,815
It's hard on lawmen.

770
01:17:18,900 --> 01:17:21,733
Hard enough to put two of them
in the ground over the last three years.

771
01:17:21,820 --> 01:17:23,697
Well, who's in charge?

772
01:17:23,780 --> 01:17:27,773
Well, the town sort of works on
a live-and-let-live basis with

773
01:17:28,300 --> 01:17:30,768
a touch of every man for himself thrown in.

774
01:17:31,460 --> 01:17:35,976
Ain't the kind of place where you check
your firearms when you get to town.

775
01:17:36,060 --> 01:17:37,209
One minute.

776
01:17:37,300 --> 01:17:40,053
Biggest operator is Miss Kate Becker.

777
01:17:40,860 --> 01:17:44,091
Big Rump Kate.
She runs the Southern Cross Saloon.

778
01:17:50,060 --> 01:17:52,051
Who are them girls, anyway?

779
01:17:52,700 --> 01:17:53,974
They're with me.

780
01:17:54,060 --> 01:17:56,528
Well, these rooms are for sleeping,
not for cooching.

781
01:17:56,620 --> 01:18:00,215
Good. Because these girls are tired
and they need their sleep.

782
01:18:00,940 --> 01:18:03,773
Well, that room down at the end
has got cots for six men,

783
01:18:03,860 --> 01:18:06,579
so I guess you ought to have enough space.

784
01:18:09,820 --> 01:18:11,731
You know where a fellow can get a bath?

785
01:18:57,460 --> 01:18:59,496
- You speak English?
- Yes.

786
01:19:00,100 --> 01:19:05,094
- My name's Tom Harte. What's your name?
- Lung Hay. My name is Lung Hay.

787
01:19:05,700 --> 01:19:06,928
Long Hay.

788
01:19:07,180 --> 01:19:08,852
Dragon. Lung.

789
01:19:09,540 --> 01:19:10,689
Dragon.

790
01:19:14,020 --> 01:19:15,578
Well, Mr Lung Hay,

791
01:19:16,540 --> 01:19:18,849
through a series of circumstances,

792
01:19:18,940 --> 01:19:23,411
fate has placed four Chinese girls
in the hands of me and my uncle.

793
01:19:25,220 --> 01:19:27,575
They got room for our horses
over at the livery.

794
01:19:27,660 --> 01:19:29,332
- Good.
- Who's this?

795
01:19:29,540 --> 01:19:32,691
- He's our new interpreter, Mr Lung Hay.
- Lung Hay.

796
01:19:33,500 --> 01:19:35,252
Lord knows we need it.

797
01:19:53,060 --> 01:19:54,334
All right.

798
01:19:54,540 --> 01:19:57,737
Tell them that I'm sorry about
everything that's happened to them.

799
01:19:57,820 --> 01:20:01,972
But we'll try and find a safe place for them.
No harm will come to them.

800
01:20:11,180 --> 01:20:15,378
They say they want to stay with you.
Please to be good as to not leave them.

801
01:20:15,460 --> 01:20:18,293
No, no.
No, they can't live on the trail with us.

802
01:20:20,420 --> 01:20:21,819
Ask him why.

803
01:20:24,380 --> 01:20:27,850
This is an old story.
There's no place safe for them.

804
01:20:28,380 --> 01:20:29,574
Nowhere.

805
01:20:30,340 --> 01:20:34,094
They will be like meat before hungry dogs.
They'll be devoured.

806
01:20:34,420 --> 01:20:36,172
Not to make you angry,

807
01:20:36,260 --> 01:20:40,378
but it would be more of a kindness
to cut their throats than to leave them here.

808
01:20:40,860 --> 01:20:42,134
But they can't stay with us.

809
01:20:42,220 --> 01:20:45,018
We've got to get our horses
through the passes before winter.

810
01:20:45,820 --> 01:20:48,653
This whole land is not safe.
You tell him that.

811
01:20:50,780 --> 01:20:53,089
Could you watch them
while we go get some supper

812
01:20:53,180 --> 01:20:55,819
and maybe feed them some of your food?

813
01:20:56,380 --> 01:20:58,098
- Yes, I can do.
- Thank you, sir.

814
01:21:09,980 --> 01:21:13,939
<i>Goodbye, Old Paint, I'm leaving Cheyenne</i>

815
01:21:14,700 --> 01:21:17,772
<i>Goodbye, Old Paint, I'm leaving Cheyenne</i>

816
01:21:18,460 --> 01:21:20,530
<i>Leaving Cheyenne</i>

817
01:21:20,620 --> 01:21:22,292
<i>On to Montana</i>

818
01:21:23,140 --> 01:21:24,937
<i>Goodbye, Old Paint</i>

819
01:21:26,300 --> 01:21:28,211
<i>leaving Cheyenne</i>

820
01:21:28,300 --> 01:21:30,211
<i>Goodbye, Old Paint</i>

821
01:21:31,620 --> 01:21:33,929
<i>leaving Cheyenne</i>

822
01:21:39,260 --> 01:21:40,818
My little girls.

823
01:21:43,980 --> 01:21:45,299
<i>Adis,</i>

824
01:21:46,300 --> 01:21:48,256
One, Three, Four and Five.

825
01:21:58,820 --> 01:22:01,573
It seems like we're drifting from our purpose

826
01:22:01,820 --> 01:22:04,380
of delivering those horses to Sheridan.

827
01:22:04,460 --> 01:22:08,055
But I'm not as hard-hearted
about those girls as you might think.

828
01:22:09,820 --> 01:22:12,618
I'm not gonna just chuck them
at the first opportunity.

829
01:22:14,300 --> 01:22:16,018
Nobility, no boundaries.

830
01:22:19,860 --> 01:22:22,772
- Evening, gents.
- Evening, ma'am.

831
01:22:23,540 --> 01:22:25,610
I'm Kate Becker. Big Rump Kate.

832
01:22:25,700 --> 01:22:27,816
How's your supper? You doing all right?

833
01:22:27,900 --> 01:22:29,333
We are, thank you.

834
01:22:29,420 --> 01:22:31,536
Nothing like a bath, some clean britches,

835
01:22:31,620 --> 01:22:34,293
a little whisky and a steak
to make a man feel almost human again.

836
01:22:34,380 --> 01:22:37,099
Well, that ain't all a man need to feel human.

837
01:22:37,180 --> 01:22:40,855
How about finishing off the evening
with some high-dollar sporting gals?

838
01:22:40,940 --> 01:22:45,092
Well, I reckon a fellow can only handle
so much humanity at one time, ma'am.

839
01:22:45,540 --> 01:22:46,768
Hey, Rose.

840
01:22:48,100 --> 01:22:52,013
I call her my English Rose. Newest gal
to work the line. Come here, sweetie.

841
01:22:52,340 --> 01:22:56,538
Rose, we got a stout lad here that
needs the knots worked out of him.

842
01:22:59,420 --> 01:23:03,095
I think I speak for both of us
when I say I think we'll pass.

843
01:23:03,780 --> 01:23:07,409
Well, maybe you prefer getting some trim
from those Celestials you brung into town.

844
01:23:09,420 --> 01:23:12,093
You boys thinking about
getting into the skin trade?

845
01:23:12,180 --> 01:23:13,818
Well, let me set you straight.

846
01:23:15,420 --> 01:23:18,856
The gold I mine from this burg,
I don't get from digging.

847
01:23:19,540 --> 01:23:22,259
There ain't a shot of whisky,
a hand of poker,

848
01:23:22,340 --> 01:23:25,855
or any fellow that wants to dip his wick
that I don't get a cut of.

849
01:23:25,940 --> 01:23:27,976
We're just passing through.

850
01:23:28,460 --> 01:23:31,736
You know about a Billy Fender?
Captain Billy Fender?

851
01:23:32,220 --> 01:23:34,814
Those girls were bought and paid for,
and you know it.

852
01:23:34,900 --> 01:23:37,175
I don't give a damn about Billy Fender.

853
01:23:37,660 --> 01:23:39,093
But they're mine!

854
01:23:46,660 --> 01:23:48,776
Well, it's a stupid sack of shit

855
01:23:48,860 --> 01:23:52,250
who believes he can waltz into this country
with a wagon full of women

856
01:23:52,340 --> 01:23:54,092
and thinks he ain't in for trouble.

857
01:23:54,860 --> 01:23:56,816
You kiss your mama with that mouth?

858
01:23:59,460 --> 01:24:01,576
What do you take for your troubles?

859
01:24:01,660 --> 01:24:05,016
We came here to eat and
have a little bit of whisky. That's it.

860
01:24:05,660 --> 01:24:09,175
Come on, mister. Everything has a price.

861
01:24:10,980 --> 01:24:12,459
Not everything.

862
01:24:18,380 --> 01:24:19,574
Come on, Rose.

863
01:24:41,700 --> 01:24:42,974
What's going on?

864
01:24:50,780 --> 01:24:52,452
Come on, damn it!

865
01:25:01,500 --> 01:25:02,853
Hold her still!

866
01:25:04,540 --> 01:25:07,100
Come on, darling.
You know you want it. Come on!

867
01:25:32,620 --> 01:25:33,848
Stay down!

868
01:25:40,380 --> 01:25:42,211
Get over here. Get over here.

869
01:25:42,300 --> 01:25:43,335
Stay back.

870
01:25:43,420 --> 01:25:45,536
You girls get together. Stay back.

871
01:25:49,180 --> 01:25:51,853
You like to spoil women? Do you?

872
01:26:06,620 --> 01:26:07,848
Come on.

873
01:26:12,060 --> 01:26:14,733
- Will you take me with you?
- Go on.

874
01:26:15,260 --> 01:26:16,534
Come on.

875
01:26:22,500 --> 01:26:23,649
Come on.

876
01:27:10,260 --> 01:27:11,295
Boys.

877
01:27:11,820 --> 01:27:15,415
You ready to donate your nuts?
Get your hands away from those pistols.

878
01:27:15,500 --> 01:27:16,933
Do it now!

879
01:27:21,020 --> 01:27:22,419
What about my property?

880
01:27:22,500 --> 01:27:26,459
That's the price of being a capitalist, lady.
Now back off!

881
01:27:28,700 --> 01:27:29,769
Heck.

882
01:27:31,060 --> 01:27:32,459
Let's go, Heck.

883
01:27:40,260 --> 01:27:44,617
Just remember,
it's money that greases the wheels, mister.

